Neither would you face defeat
Invincible almost
As long as your heart remained free

The ones you love would fall
And the ones you hate would grow strong
Such was the price of immortality.

So he went to war with a rose 
And held those who stood against so very close
Loved his enemies more than he could
And drove away anyone who said,
" I'll be always standing by you for good".
